The purpose of the [inset prop](https://material-ui.com/api/list-item-text/#props) on `ListItemText` is to align text of items that don&#39;t have an icon with the text of items that do (see the [Inset List demo](https://material-ui.com/components/lists/#inset-list)). It is **not** for indenting nested list items.

If you look at the [Nested List demo](https://material-ui.com/components/lists/#nested-list), you will find that the indent is done via `paddingLeft` applied to the nested list items. In the demo, this is set to 32px (`theme.spacing(4)`), but you can set this to whatever you want it to be.

Here is the [code](https://codesandbox.io/s/bhnby) from the Nested List demo:

